# Gen-AI Feature Guide

## Data Flow

```
User prompt
  -> useGenAI.sendPrompt()
  -> LLM returns { actions, ui }
  -> actions executed via action-adapter.ts (creates/updates canvas objects)
  -> ui spec stored as genAiSpec on the root frame
  -> CustomControlsPopover renders the ui spec as interactive controls
  -> Control changes either:
     a) Re-run the generator function (if spec.generate exists)
     b) Execute the control's individual action template
  -> Canvas updates dispatched, values stamped back into genAiSpec
```

## Key Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `hooks/useGenAI.ts` | Chat state (per-frame), streaming, prompt dispatch, generator execution |
| `adapter/action-adapter.ts` | Maps action descriptors to canvas store dispatches |
| `adapter/fill-converter.ts` | Converts between gen-ai fill formats and canvas fill types |
| `components/CustomControlsSection.tsx` | "Custom" section in properties panel, "+" auto-generate button, multi-object support |
| `components/CustomControlsPopover.tsx` | Renders UISpec controls, manages values, persists state |
| `runtime/codegen.ts` | Compiles and executes generator functions |
| `runtime/template.ts` | Control defaults, placeholder resolution, `collectControlDefaults` |
| `prompt/system-prompt.ts` | LLM instructions — action format, control types, recipes, `AUTO_GENERATE_ADDENDUM` |
| `prompt/prompt-composer.ts` | Assembles system prompt + context + history, supports `autoGenerate` option |
| `utils/intent.ts` | `isGenAiIntent()` regex for routing prompts |

## Chat History

Chat history is scoped per frame ID via `chatHistoryMapRef` (a `Map<string, GenAIChatMessage[]>`).
Each frame with controls gets its own conversation thread. Switching between objects isolates context.
Auto-generate (`opts.autoGenerate`) is a one-shot operation — it skips history entirely (no read, no write).
`/clear` slash command calls `clearHistory()` to wipe all frame histories.

## Value Persistence (specWithCurrentValues)

When control values change:
1. `CustomControlsPopover.persistValues` stamps current values into `spec.controls[].props.defaultValue`
2. The stamped spec is saved as `genAiSpec` JSON on the canvas object
3. `genAiValues` JSON is saved alongside as a fallback
4. On popover reopen, `loadPersistedValues` reads stamped `defaultValue` first, then `genAiValues`, then reads from canvas

## Modify Pipeline

When modifying an existing gen-ai object:
1. `restoreFromFrame(frameId, genAiSpec)` is called to set context
2. `sendPrompt(message)` merges the LLM response with the existing spec
3. `rewriteActionsForReapply` retargets all actions to the existing frame
4. Generator re-runs with current values (stamped defaults + persisted values)

## Auto-Generate (Reverse-Engineer Controls)

Triggered by the "+" button in CustomControlsSection:
1. Dispatches `"gen-ai-auto-generate"` event with selected object IDs
2. `AiAssistantSidebar` listens, calls `sendPrompt("auto-generate", { autoGenerate: true, targetObjectId })`
3. `composePrompt` uses `AUTO_GENERATE_ADDENDUM` as the system prompt (in `system-prompt.ts`)
4. LLM analyzes the selected nodes and returns controls (no generator, no actions typically)
5. Spec is persisted on `targetObjectId` (the existing object)
6. Controls popover opens automatically on completion

Key: `targetObjectId` prevents `replace: true` from clearing `rootFrameIdRef` (which would lose the target).

## AI Shimmer Animation

All gen-ai LLM calls activate the shimmer via `setAiEditingObjectsGroup` in `runGenAiWithChat`.
The shimmer covers initial generation, follow-up modifications, and auto-generate.
The star icon on the canvas also enters loading state when `aiEditingGroups` overlaps the selection
(checked in `OnCanvasAiPrompt.tsx` via `selectionInAiEditingGroup`).

## Control Types

- `slider` / `range`: Numeric sliders
- `color`: Single solid color picker
- `fill`: Multi-stop gradient/fill picker (FigUI3 `fig-input-fill`). Always use this for gradients.
- `select` / `radio`: Enumerated options
- `checkbox` / `toggle`: Boolean
- `text`: String input
- `xy-pad`: 2D offset/position control. Never use for width/height (use sliders instead).
- `angle`: Rotation/angle dial

## Control Size (Layout)

- `size` (optional top-level field on each control, NOT inside `props`):
  - `"large"` (default): horizontal row, label 1/3 + control 2/3
  - `"small"`: horizontal row, label 1/2 + control 1/2 (compact)
  - `"xl"`: vertical layout, label above + control full width
- All controls default to `"large"`. Set `"xl"` explicitly for controls that need full width.

## Slash Commands

- `/status` — Claude API connection, rate limits, credits
- `/clear` — Clear all gen-ai per-frame chat histories
- `/ui [type] [size]` — Preview control widgets (optional size: large, small, xl)
- `/help` — List available commands
